# Q2. Install Cert Manager

### Question

Install cert-manager using Helm in Namespace `cert-manager`.

* Create Namespace cert-manager
* Install Helm chart jetstack/cert-manager (`crds.enabled=true`)
* Release name: cert-manager
* Update ClusterIssuer YAML to include:

```yaml
spec:
  selfSigned:
    crlDistributionPoints:
    - http://example.com/crl
```

* Apply ClusterIssuer

### Fast Search

```text
cert-manager helm install
```

### Solution

```bash
kubectl create ns cert-manager
```

```bash
helm repo add jetstack https://charts.jetstack.io
helm repo update
```

```bash
helm install cert-manager \
jetstack/cert-manager \
-n cert-manager \
--set crds.enabled=true
```

Edit:

```yaml
spec:
  selfSigned:
    crlDistributionPoints:
    - http://example.com/crl
```

```bash
kubectl apply -f /opt/course/2/cluster-issuer.yaml
```

