# Q9. Query Secrets Using ServiceAccount

### Question

Create Pod:

```text
api-contact
```

Image:

```text
nginx:1-alpine
```

Namespace:

```text
project-swan
```

Use ServiceAccount:

```text
secret-reader
```

Query all Secrets through Kubernetes API.

Save result:

```bash
/opt/course/9/result.json
```

### Solution

Pod:

```yaml
serviceAccountName: secret-reader
```

Exec:

```bash
kubectl exec -it api-contact \
-n project-swan -- sh
```

```bash
TOKEN=$(cat /var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token)
```

```bash
apk add curl
```

```bash
curl -k \
-H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" \
https://kubernetes.default.svc/api/v1/namespaces/project-swan/secrets
```

Save output to:

```bash
/opt/course/9/result.json
```

